      "message": "1. Spelling: Implemented.\n\n2. Commit messages should be written in the present tense (“Implement,” not “Implemented.”)\n\n3. nit: so that “git shortlog” works well, it’s a git best practice for the first line of a commit message to be a short summary, no longer than 72 characters, and to not end it with a period.",
      "revId": "20e19b2def723d5c2a68e6f4aaf09a462947f2cc",
