      "writtenOn": "2017-02-27T16:37:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Never call sprintf(), always use snprintf(). The buffer length is important, even if you don’t think that the buffer can overflow.\n\nsnprintf(path, sizeof(path), \"/proc/%d/status\", pid);\n\nAnd then it’s acceptable (optional, but at least safe) to size path[] to be exactly long as the longest string you’d see given the data types involved, plus room for the NUL terminator: char path[25].",
      "revId": "20e19b2def723d5c2a68e6f4aaf09a462947f2cc",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
